# Dual-Approach Workflow (conv-nav / tab-nav)

This repo runs two parallel navigation experiments alongside `main`.

## Branches and worktrees

| Track | Branch | Worktree | Vercel URL |
|-------|--------|----------|------------|
| conv-nav | `conv-nav` | `/Users/timcherny/DevRev-conv-nav` | https://dev-rev-conv-nav.vercel.app |
| tab-nav | `tab-nav` | `/Users/timcherny/DevRev-tab-nav` | https://dev-rev-tab-nav.vercel.app |
| production | `main` | `/Users/timcherny/DevRev` | https://dev-rev-app.vercel.app |

`tab-nav` was seeded from `nav-tab`. `conv-nav` was seeded from `main`.

## Deploy commands

- `npm run deploy` — main app only (`dev-rev-app`). After a successful deploy, follow the deploy-push-main rule and push `main`.
- `npm run deploy:conv-nav` — conv-nav project only. Push **only** `conv-nav`; never merge or push to `main`.
- `npm run deploy:tab-nav` — tab-nav project only. Push **only** `tab-nav`; never merge or push to `main`.

## Local dev

- conv-nav worktree: `npm run dev:conv-nav` (port 5173)
- tab-nav worktree: `npm run dev:tab-nav` (port 5174)

## Cross-track fixes

When a fix on `main` should land in both experiments, merge or cherry-pick into each worktree:

```bash
git fetch origin
git merge origin/main
```

## Merging a winner

Merge the chosen branch into `main` in the main worktree, then `npm run deploy` for production. Cherry-pick from the other branch if needed before retiring it.
